Package com.github.mavolin.maxon.jsonvalues

Class JsonPrimitive

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mavolin.maxon.jsonvalues.JsonPrimitive
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JsonValue
    public class JsonPrimitive
extends java.lang.Object
implements JsonValue
    JsonPrimitive represents all four JSON primitive types: Nulls, Booleans, Numbers and Strings. It acts like a wrapper through which the values can be extracted using their respective Java representation. Additionally this will provide support for chars, which are represented as a one character JSON String, as there is no JSON equivalent.
